After trial and error I have finally settled down with a blog to to work with. I looked into hosting a wordpress server using AWS distributed by Bitnami. The cost of the server was .019 per hour which makes about $13.68 a month, or $164.16 a year. 

Convience and cost is what you get with the personal plan from wordpress. For $4 month you get 6 GBs of storage and a free domain. I gave it a test run and immediately was pushed away with the all the premium features that were encouraged. Theme and even colors for the free layout cost money. I took advantage of the 14-day money back guarrantee.

I went to github to host my resume statically, and was gonna call it the end of the project. However, looking into the documentation I notice there is blogging capabiltiy using Jekyll and github actions. 

Here we are. Using Ruby, Jekyll, Gihub, and nvim.I did run into issues by installing an outdated Ruby software that I belive was because I installed it using elevated SUDO privleges. Uninstalling and reinstalling, and properly following the installation guide, I have everything up and running. I am able to run my blog using my Linux Mint Laptop!

